stories.title: West Indies relapse
stories.summary:
Bristol-It is far too early to pessimistically proclaim an end to the
West Indies revival under Jimmy Adams and the new management team

stories.title: Colour, Music, Light - Southern Hemisphere cricket comes to England
stories.summary:
The crowd may have been seventy thousand less for a day-nighter, but the
colour, the music and the lights ensured that in atmosphere, the little ground did not lack much behind the imposing MCG, Down Under

stories.title: Zimbabwe shock win brings NatWest Series to life
stories.summary:
Bristol, NatWest Series: West Indies (232 for seven off 50 overs) lost to
Zimbabwe (233 for four off 45 overs) by six wickets

stories.title: Zimbabwe up with scoring rate
stories.summary:
Some fine batting by Zimbabwe, their innings held together by a restrained
Neil Johnson, has kept them on even terms in the NatWest Series match at
Bristol with a West Indian team thatprobably did not expect such stern opposition

stories.title: Lara leads harvest of fifties
stories.summary:
On a slowish pitch where quick scoring was never very easy, West Indies
achieved what was probably the match-winning total of 232 for seven off an
accurate but essentially toothless Zimbabwe attack

stories.title: West Indies accelerate after steady start
stories.summary:
Bryan Strang, bowling speed in the lower seventies, opened for Zimbabwe to
Adrian Griffith of West Indies in the NatWest Series limited-overs match at
Bristol -  two singles nudged to third man coming off his first over

stories.title: NatWest Series under way - and the sun shines through
stories.summary:
The NatWest Series opened in Bristol under rather better weather than during
the previous few days, warm and humid, with the sun often shining through
the haze

stories.title: Bracewell signs up for another three years
stories.summary: John Bracewell's curriculum vitae is starting to get a distinct bulge in it and Gloucestershire continues to be the main beneficiary of his expertise

stories.title: 1st Match, West Indies v Zimbabwe, Statistical Highlights
stories.summary: It was the 1605th ODI in cricket history

stories.title: West Indies relapse
stories.summary:
Bristol-It is far too early to pessimistically proclaim an end to the
West Indies revival under Jimmy Adams and the new management team
